page.title: 15PRESTATYN- WOODLAND BIRDLIFE
page.content: The birdlife of the Prestatyn area is rich both in terms of sheer numbers and diversity of species. The woodland residents include Blue, Great and Coal Tits in abundance also Marsh and Long-Tailed-Tits,Nuthatches, Treecreepers,Goldcrests,Greater Spotted Woodpeckers,Bullfinches,Tawny Owls, Sparrowhawks,Mistle Thrushes, Jays and Stock Doves are common.Willow Tits,Lesser Spotted and Green Woodpeckers are also occasionally seen.In Summer the woods are filled with the sounds of Willow-Warblers, Chiffchaffs,Blackcaps and Garden Warblers,other migrants occurring including Spotted and Pied lycatchers. In Winter the hawthorn berries attract Redwing and Fieldfare.Redpolls and Siskins are also to be seen at most seasons.
